title._content: Pontiac showroom, York St, Sydney, January 1940, by Sam Hood

tag.raw: State Library of New South Wales
tag.author: 29454428@N08

description._content: Notes: 'The movie 'Mr Smith Goes to Washington' featured a Pontiac Chieftain, so Stack & Company, York Street Pontiac dealers used a still from the movie in their window display. Stack & Co. was started by William J. Stack in 1935. He had the Chevrolet and Pontiac dealership and later, also Holden.' From Sydney Exposures... [by] Alan Davies (1991), p. 88.
